  "prompt": "What language do babies think in?",
  "response": "Babies primarily think in sensory and emotional experiences rather than a specific language. Early in life, thought processes are closely tied to sensations, feelings, and basic needs. As they grow and are exposed to spoken language, they begin to internalize and understand words and concepts, eventually developing the ability to think in terms of the language(s) they are exposed to. Initially, though, their thoughts are more about perceptions, images, and emotions rather than structured language.",
